punchClock

Class Money

  • java.lang.Object
    • punchClock.Money

  • public class Money
extends java.lang.Object
    The Money class handles all actions and calculations regarding currency earned during the work week. This class also contains methods to convert one currency to another.
    Author:
    Freeman Ogburn, Tyler Hay, Max Jensen

      • calcGrossEarnings

        public double calcGrossEarnings(double time,
                                double rate,
                                int currency)
        Calculates total earnings with the time and rate passed in.
        Parameters:
        time - numerical time value in milliseconds
        rate - numerical value representing dollar earnings per hour
        currency - index of selected currency location
        Returns:
        Product of time and rate that represents total earnings

      • taxAmounts

        public double taxAmounts(double federal,
                         double soc,
                         double med,
                         double state,
                         double grossPay)
        taxAmounts method is the updated version of calcNetEarnings. The method takes in all of the double values from the Tax text fields and converts the to a percentage value, it will then calculate and return the net pay by multiplying these taxes to the gross pay.
        Parameters:
        federal - Federal Tax value
        soc - Social Security Tax value
        med - Medicare Tax value
        state - State Tax value
        grossPay - Gross Pay value
        Returns:
        Double Net Pay value.

      • getOT

        public boolean getOT()
        Getter method for Overtime variable.
        Returns:
        boolean value 0 for false and 1 for true
